-- Uncertainty on Emissions Pricing Delays Australia Investment, Combet Says
-- B y   M a r i o n   R a e
-- 2010-10-18T03:45:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/uncertainty-on-emissions-pricing-delays-australia-investment-combet-says.html
Australia has “billions of
dollars” of investment tied up because of uncertainty about
putting a price on carbon, and business leaders accept that
reform is “necessary,” Climate Change and Energy Efficiency
Minister Greg Combet told parliament today after the government
set up a business roundtable to advise the government on a plan
to tackle emissions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
